      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix and split the batter",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 180°C (160°C fan). Line a 900 g (2 lb) loaf tin with baking paper. Beat {{unsalted-butter}} and {{caster-sugar}} until pale and fluffy. Add {{vanilla-extract}}, then beat in the {{eggs}} one at a time. Fold in {{self-raising-flour}} and {{whole-milk}}. Spoon half the batter into a separate bowl. Stir {{cocoa-powder}} into the second bowl and mix until uniform.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Layer, swirl, and bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Drop alternate spoonfuls of vanilla and chocolate batter into the tin, 3 or 4 spoons of each, alternating, so the tin fills evenly. Draw a skewer or knife through the batter in two or three S-shapes lengthwise. Do not stir or fold. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes until a skewer inserted in the centre comes out clean. Cool in the tin for 10 minutes, then turn onto a rack.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
